  <section>
        <h2>Loops</h2>
        <p>
        Python provides <code>for</code> and <code>while</code> loops for iteration. 
        The <code>for</code> loop is commonly used with the <code>range()</code> function or to iterate 
        over sequences.
        </p>
    
        <pre><code>
            # While loop
            count = 5
            while count > 0:
                print(count)
                count -= 1

            # For loop with range
            for i in range(5):
                print(i)  # Prints 0 to 4

            # For loop with list
            fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
            for fruit in fruits:
                print(fruit)

            # For loop with range (start, stop, step)
            for i in range(2, 10, 2):
                print(i)  # Prints 2, 4, 6, 8

            # List comprehension (Pythonic way)
            squares = [x**2 for x in range(5)]
            print(squares)

            # Break and continue
            for i in range(10):
                if i == 5:
                    break  # Exit loop
                if i % 2 == 0:
                    continue  # Skip to next iteration
            print(i)
        </code></pre>
